title: Timbered Building, Strassburg
medium: Graphite on cream paperboard tipped into binding with fabric
description: Vertical sheet depicting a multi-story timbered building with very steep tiled roof.  The building is seen from a canted corner, and only its upper levels are illustrated.  The roof has two tiers of dormers, and the roof corners terminate in finials consisting of balls on spikes.
